Package myTest

Class MapAdapterTest

java.lang.Object
myTest.MapAdapterTest
public class MapAdapterTest
extends java.lang.Object
Test class for MapAdapter
See Also:
HMap, MapAdapter
Test Suite Summary:
This test suite is in charge of testing the MapAdapter class. The target of this test suite is to verify that the adapter class MapAdapter behaves as described in the HMap interface.
Test Suite Design:
Each individual method will be tested in multiple scenarios to verify that the behavior is the one expected. Both standard and exceptional situations will be tested to verify that unconventional operation are managed correctly without compromising the execution.
Test Suite Pre-Condition and Execution Variables:
An initially empty HMap (the subject of the tests) and HCollection (that will help checking the functionalities) that will be manipulated in the test cases. Execution variables are initialized in before().
Test Suite Post-Condition:
The behavior of MapAdapter is expected to be the same as described in the HMap interface.
Test Suite Test Cases:
See Test cases in Method Summary below.
